{'text': 'The last day of the Moonshot Crowdfunding Campaign is here! This is our final shot to send your name to the Moon with Iris! ⁠
⁠
We are currently at $40,000 out of our $50,000 goal. Please consider donating to support the world‚Äôs first nano, non-governmental, university-initiated, and student-developed rover that will operate beyond planet Earth. Anyone who makes a gift through our crowdfunding page will be added to a list of names that will be aboard Iris‚Äôs memory at launch and be a part of history!⁠

{'text': 'The Tartans are on a tear with their fourth straight doubleheader sweep and fifth of the season! Sophomore Megan Hu (pictured) was 6-for-8 today and singled in the game-winning run with two outs in the seventh inning in game two. @carnegiemellonsoftball \nüì∑ by @carnegiemellon.hdic \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonSoftball #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'The @tartantennis men remained undefeated against Division III opponents with a 5-3 win against #14 Kenyon today. Sophomore Raahil Doshi (pictured) earned two points for the Tartans with a win at third doubles with freshman Michael Fourchy and the match-clinching win at fourth singles. \nüì∑ by @carnegiemellon.hdic \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonTennis #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'Junior Gwen Delacruz (pictured) did it all in game 1 for @carnegiemellonsoftball today pitching six solid innings to earn her first win of the season. She also knocked in four runs, scored three, and was perfect at the plate with four hits. \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonSoftball #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'The Tartans picked up their 7th win (and remain undefeated) against a Division III regional opponent. Freshman Brandon Aprill (pictured) won at second singles today and is now 5-1 overall. \nüì∑ by @carnegiemellon.hdic \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonTennis #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'ICYMI - senior Bram Miller broke an 11-year old record when he threw the shot put 17.11 meters to win the event at Robert Morris on Saturday. His mark is fourth best in the nation. 

Junior Justin Kiefel also set a new school record, topping his previous record in the triple jump with a winning mark of 14.65 meters which ranks second in the nation. 
üì∑ by @carnegiemellon.hdic 
#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonTrackAndField #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'Big hits all around today for @carnegiemellonsoftball. Sophomore Isabel Bermudez (pictured) hit two home runs, the team tied a school record for hits in a game with 23, sophomore Piper Johnson was a home run shy of the cycle, junior Emily Song had three doubles in game one, and sophomore Tessa Bruneau extended her hitting streak to a program-best 10 games. \nüì∑ by @carnegiemellon.hdic \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonSoftball #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'Another tournament, another individual winner! Congrats to senior Jason Folker for his first collegiate individual medalist honor! Jason carded six birdies in the final round and led the men of @carnegiemellongolf to a second-place finish at the Wynlakes Intercollegiate in Alabama. The Tartans tied a school record for lowest two-round score. \n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonGolf #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': 'The women of @carnegiemellongolf played another great two rounds of golf, placing second at the Montgomery Country Club Women‚Äôs Intercollegiate in Alabama. They set four school records including best team two-round score, best team single round score, best individual two-round score, and best individual single round score. Congrats to all!\n#TartanProud #CarnegieMellonGolf #LifeAtCMU'}

{'text': "SASC would like to Congratulate our senior Tartan Scholar Ambassadors on their upcoming graduation! Tartan Scholar Ambassadors support Tartan Scholars students. Ambassadors provide peer support, assist with program development and execution, identify resources for academic support, serve as a liaison between each small group of students known as Tartan Scholar families, their Tartan Scholar mentors, and the Tartan Scholar staff. Tartan Scholars and Tartan Scholars Ambassadors are very much a family and this year's seniors will be deeply missed. Thank you for being a part of the SASC team and Happy Graduation! \n#CMUgrad21 #AllTartans"}

{'text': 'It‚Äôs Friday, and SASC would like to say Congratulations to our graduating Supplemental Instructors. For anyone who may not know Supplemental Instruction (SI) is, its a non-remedial approach to learning for historically difficult courses which have been challenging for ALL students. A peer led group is facilitated by an SI Leader, who is a current student who has already successfully completed the course. We definitely feel the loss when our SI Leaders graduate. Thank you for all of your hard work, and Happy Graduation!\n#CMUgrad21 #AllTartans'}

{'text': 'SASC would like to continue dedicating some time this week to our graduating student employees. Next up is our Peer Tutors! This is probably one of our most asked about services. Tutoring consists of ongoing individualized and small group sessions for students seeking support related to their coursework. You can utilize tutoring to discuss course related content, clarify and ask questions, work through practice problems, etc.  Just like all of the jobs in SASC Peer Tutoring takes hard work and dedication. We appreciate all that they do! Congratulations seniors SASC is going to miss you! \n#CMUgrad21 #AllTartans'}

{'text': 'SASC would like to dedicate some time this week to congratulate our graduating student employees. We truly appreciate everything they do for our students and for us. We admittedly get very attached to each and every one of them. Our first group is the Academic Coaches: Ella Rosenblum, Jackie Godinez, Lisa Lo, Matthew Fang, Riya Bhattacharya and Ziyi Xu \nCongratulations Seniors! SASC is going to miss you! \n#CMUgrad21 #AllTartans'}

{'text': 'Do you have questions about Disability Resources? The Student Academic Success Center is where we strive to provide responsive, reasonable accommodations to help our students accomplish their best work. Find more information on our website https://www.cmu.edu/disability-resources/ or email us with your questions at success@andrew.cmu.edu\n#AllTartans'}

{'text': 'It‚Äôs time to register and submit your presentations for Virtual Meeting of the Minds 2021! All poster and video presentations will be available to view May 10-11, with the main event on May 12.  Student presenters should be aware that attendees will have the ability to leave comments/questions on your presentations, and the student will receive an email alert.  Students should check comments on 5/12 and respond as needed.  Students will not be assigned a specific time for Q&A, but should be responsible for checking comments. Registration/submission deadline: Wednesday, May 5, 2021, 11:59 PM EDT. For more information please check out our webpage at https://www.cmu.edu/uro/MoM/index.html\nYou can also contact Jen Weidenhof if you have questions or concerns.'}
